The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Jan. 12: Reliance Communications (R-Com) is planning to list its undersea cable business unit, FLAG Telecom, in London to raise over $500 million. The company plans to dilute 20-24 per cent stake in the wholly owned firm through the listing on LSE. Sources said the preparation for the listing would start next month.

 New Delhi, Jan. 12: Hughes will invest an undisclosed amount in the country in the next three years to scale up its presence here. It has invested over $300 million in India so far.

 New Delhi, Jan. 12: The Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC) has been invited by Maersk Oil to participate in the bidding for buying a 30 per cent stake in two Caspian Sea blocks.

 Bangalore, Jan. 12: Aviva plans to transfer 2,900 employees from EXL and WNS to Aviva Global Services (AGS) this year. Aviva has transferred over 1,600 employees at its Bangalore operations from Aviva-24/7 Customer to AGS on January 1.

 Mumbai, Jan. 12: Justice S.C. Dharmadhihari of Bombay High Court has fixed February 6 to hear the question of arbitration between the Wadia group and Danone, the two joint venture partners of Britannia. While the Wadia group has sought arbitration, Danone is opposed to such a proposal.




